  "title": "Mechanical Engineer | Vessel Mechanical Service | West",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a <strong>Marine and Offshore Industry. </strong>Due to business needs, they are now recruiting a <strong>Mechanical Engineer</strong> to be part of their Team for ongoing transformation projects. They are located in the <strong>West </strong>- easily accessible.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage all mechanical aspects of lab setups for in-house FAT, including selection of couplings and gearboxes.</li><li>Perform hands-on troubleshooting and resolve mechanical system issues throughout all project stages, including development, setup, FAT, SAT, and warranty support.</li><li>Lead mechanical system design activities across all stages of development.</li><li>Produce detailed mechanical drawings to ensure clear communication with suppliers.</li><li>Develop standardized systems and process flows to improve efficiency, reduce cycle times, and ensure consistent quality.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Hands on experience with vessel mechanical and engine systems.</li><li>Experience with engineering design software (SOLIDWORKS is a plus)</li></ul><p><em>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click </em><em><strong>APPLY NOW</strong></em><em> or email an updated copy of your resume/cv.</em></p><p><em>We regret that only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</em></p><p><em>Email Address: </em><a href=\"mailto:jobs@recruitpedia.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>jobs@recruitpedia.sg</em></a></p><p><em>Recruitpedia Pte. Ltd.</em></p><p><em>EA License No: 19C9682</em></p><p><em>EA Personnel No: R25157233 (Loh Pooi Keng)</em></p>",
